doc_summary_long: A South Carolina high school student was arrested Thursday after allegedly posting 'Florida Round 2' on Snapchat -- an obvious reference to Wednesday's school shooting -- but insisted that the post was simply a 'joke.' Officials said the post, which was sent via Snapchat, showed a teen wearing a partial mask and holding what looked like an assault rifle. Officials at Broome High School received an anonymous tip from a student about a possible threat, Spartanburg School District Three spokeswoman Sherri Horton said.
doc_summary_short: A South Carolina high school student was arrested Thursday after allegedly posting 'Florida Round 2' on Snapchat -- an obvious reference to Wednesday's school shooting -- but insisted that the post was simply a 'joke.'
doc_title: South Carolina HS student who allegedly posted 'Florida Round 2,' tells cops it was a joke
